I&#39;m using a machine with 4 disks. Heritrix directory is on /0. The 
directories of warc.gz files are /1, /2, and /3. I tried to reduce the 
size of the heritrix/jobs/My-Job directory. I took a checkpoint one time 
per two days and gzip the log files of the checkpoint. But, the state 
directory increased very fast:

root@My-Machine:/0/heritrix/jobs/My-Job# du -hs *
0    action
880K    checkpoints
24K    crawler-beans.cxml
4.0K    job.log
0    job.log.lck
12G    logs
108K    negative-surts.dump
8.0K    scratch
112K    seeds.txt
*236G    state*
100K    surts.dump

The problem is that /0 is fully used now:

~# df -h /?
Filesystem            Size  Used Avail Use% Mounted on
/dev/sda1             252G  252G     0 100% /0
/dev/sdb1             373G   61G  313G  17% /1
/dev/sdc1             373G   60G  314G  16% /2
/dev/sdd1             373G   59G  315G  16% /3

My solution is to start a new job and put frontier.recover.gz in action 
directory to continue crawling uncrawled URIs and remove state directory 
from the previous job, is this solution reasonable? I want to ask too 
about the size i have to provide to continue crawling without filling up 
the size by .jdb files in state directory.

